":"300 g water"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"500 g large raw prawns, peeled and deveined (approx. 1 kg prawns in their shells)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"2 - 4 limes, sliced (2-3 mm)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"200 g fennel bulb, sliced thinly (1-2 mm)"},{"isHeader":false,"content":"400 g cherry tomatoes, halved"}],"nutrition":["per 1 portion","785 kJ \/ 187 kcal","17 g","6 g","10 g"],"hintsAndTricks":["<i>This bright salad is bursting with fresh Italian flavours. Lightly steamed, the onions become more mellow, and with the tomatoes and fennel they form a delicious backdrop to the juicy prawns.<\/i>","Add toasted pine nuts for extra flavour, as is often done in Sicily.","If using frozen prawns, they should be defrosted before starting the recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","40m","6 portions"]}